contemporary political economic or social change in the asia pacific region including northeast southeast and south asia or topics in international relations and international political economy the fellow will take part in center activities throughout the academic year and present their research findings in center seminars they will also participate in the center's publication program the fellowship is made possible through the generosity of walter h shorenstein shorenstein fellowships in contemporary asia shorenstein aparc fellowship for postdoctoral scholars professionals international scholars not accepting applications at this time search fsi search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages news of interest we are accepting applications for our 2012 2013 fellowship programs december 15 2011 cisac fsi stanford announcement cddrl now accepting applications for pre and postdoctoral fellowship november 8 2011 cddrl announcement cddrl hewlett fellowships now accepting applications november 3 2009 cddrl draper hills summer fellows program announcement shorenstein aparc announces new fellowships and faculty searches for the 2010 2011 academic year september 9 2009 shorenstein aparc news shorenstein aparc invites applications for two new academic positions in japanese and korean studies july 29 2007 fsi stanford shorenstein aparc announcement aparc renamed the walter h shorenstein asia pacific research center september 20 2005 shorenstein aparc press release support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 4581 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
